The paper focuses on reinforcement learning with deep neural networks, specifically in the context of autonomous driving. This suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given the emphasis on deep learning and neural networks, as well as the use of visual sensors, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories. However, the focus on autonomous driving and robotics also suggests cs.RO and cs.SY as possible categories, while the use of reinforcement learning and policy optimization suggests cs.AI as another possible category.
